



Sir
Richmond Decemr. 25th. 1780.



The inclosed Instructions given by me to Capt. Lockhart for conducting on the Prisoners taken at Kings Mountain, and his [239] report, of which a Copy is also inclosed, will inform Your Excellency in what manner these Prisoners are disposed of. I have the honor to be with the highest respect Your Excellencys most obedient and most humbl Servt,

Th: Jefferson

